 4-bit group)\n    *   End Index = $4 \times \text{sel} + 3$ (the MSB of the 4-bit group)\n    *   The assignment will be: `assign out = in[(sel*4)+3 : sel*4];`\n\nThis assignment correctly performs the selection required by the problem statement.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input  logic [1023:0] in,\n    input  logic [7:0] sel,\n    output logic [3:0] out\n);\n\n    // The multiplexer selects a 4-bit chunk from the 1024-bit input 'in'.\n    // 'sel' (8 bits) determines which of the 256 chunks (0 to 255) to select.\n    // The i-th chunk starts at bit index i*4.\n    // We need to select the 4 bits starting at index (sel * 4) up to (sel * 4) + 3.\n    \n    // SystemVerilog allows direct slicing: in[MSB:LSB].\n    // MSB index: (sel * 4) + 3\n    // LSB index: (sel * 4)\n    assign out = in[(sel * 4) + 3 : (sel * 4)];\n\nendmodule"
